{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PdCUvfavvCYGEDBWGfkkXV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: structured-logging-contract\n     3→description: Insert consistent method/step structured logging lines into target functions using jig.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# Structured Logging Contract (Jig)\n     7→\n     8→Use this skill to enforce stable observability signals.\n     9→\n    10→## Required Variables\n    11→\n    12→- `target_file`\n    13→- `function_name`\n    14→- `event_namespace`\n    15→- `step_name`\n    16→- `entity_id_expr`\n    17→\n    18→## Usage\n    19→\n    20→```bash\n    21→jig run ${CLAUDE_SKILL_DIR}/recipe.yaml --vars '{\n    22→  \"target_file\": \"services/core_service.py\",\n    23→  \"function_name\": \"create_record\",\n    24→  \"event_namespace\": \"core_service.create_record\",\n    25→  \"step_name\": \"validate_input\",\n    26→  \"entity_id_expr\": \"record_id if \\\"record_id\\\" in locals() else None\"\n    27→}'\n    28→```\n    29→\n    30→Notes:\n    31→- Patch anchors target the first function in `target_file`.\n    32→- Keep one primary function per target file when using this recipe.\n    33→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a28ca082-b3de-46b4-8c63-29b247045928","uuid":"ddeb021e-da8a-4e34-967a-0ba6edc292c9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018eW3ZedmpUaLKgKDd86t95","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→name: structured-logging-contract\n     2→description: Add standardized start/end structured log statements to a function\n     3→\n     4→variables:\n     5→  target_file:\n     6→    type: string\n     7→    required: true\n     8→  function_name:\n     9→    type: string\n    10→    required: true\n    11→  event_namespace:\n    12→    type: string\n    13→    required: true\n    14→  step_name:\n    15→    type: string\n    16→    required: true\n    17→  entity_id_expr:\n    18→    type: string\n    19→    required: true\n    20→\n    21→files:\n    22→  - template: templates/logger_setup.py.j2\n    23→    inject: \"{{ target_file }}\"\n    24→    after: '^(from|import) '\n    25→    at: last\n    26→    skip_if: 'logger = logging.getLogger('\n    27→\n    28→  - template: templates/log_start.py.j2\n    29→    patch: \"{{ target_file }}\"\n    30→    anchor:\n    31→      pattern: \"^def \"\n    32→      scope: function_body\n    33→      position: before\n    34→    skip_if: '\"{{ event_namespace }}.start\"'\n    35→\n    36→  - template: templates/log_done.py.j2\n    37→    patch: \"{{ target_file }}\"\n    38→    anchor:\n    39→      pattern: \"^def \"\n    40→      scope: function_body\n    41→      position: before_close\n    42→    skip_if: '\"{{ event_namespace }}.done\"'\n    43→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a28ca082-b3de-46b4-8c63-29b247045928","uuid":"b3aed1be-05d1-483a-8297-f7c721b18df7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MPiWpNgBsE7edcKpTRF6pm","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→from datetime import datetime\n     2→\n     3→\n     4→def create_record(record_id):\n     5→    timestamp = datetime.utcnow().isoformat()\n     6→    return {\n     7→        \"id\": record_id,\n     8→        \"created_at\": timestamp,\n     9→    }\n    10→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a28ca082-b3de-46b4-8c63-29b247045928","uuid":"0ec5a71a-bc61-4427-b06c-d6ab4ce53da2"}
